-- South Africa Leaves Its Wheat Crop Forecast Unchanged at 1.57 Million Tons
-- B y   C a r l i   L o u r e n s
-- 2010-12-21T13:30:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-21/south-africa-leaves-its-wheat-crop-forecast-unchanged-at-1-57-million-tons.html
South Africa left its wheat harvest
forecast unchanged at 1.57 million metric tons.  The crop forecast for barley was little changed at 213,814
tons while the canola crop outlook was reduced by 4.3 percent to
37,950 tons, Baldwin Netshifhefhe, who chaired the committee
today, said by phone from Pretoria. Planting area estimates for
the three crops were unchanged, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Carli Lourens  in Johannesburg at 
 clourens@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
